_Values: What is this...? This doesn’t look right… something's wrong here!
Lylah! There you are! I’ve been looking everywhere for you!
That voice... it sounds just like Miss Mittle. But if it is why does she look like this? I better see what she wants

Point your right controller where you want Lylah to move and press the right trigger to move her to that spot. 
To speak to characters or graffiti on buildings, stand close to them and press the right touchpad to interact. 
They may be able to give you some insight into your situation or give you information.
I understand… on your way now child. If you need help, just speak to the elder by the fountain, he always knows what’s happening around here.
This can’t be happening… can’t be real. Everything was perfect and then it was like sand falling between my fingers.
Don’t turn your back on it, face it head on and you will be just fine.
Hello young one, are you ok? I know you’re going through a hard time and you have a long road ahead of you… But you are capable.
You may find it almost impossible to come to terms with reality, but you just need to keep putting one foot in front of the other...
Where did you get to? I couldn’t find you anywhere! Nevermind that, you need to go to your Granny's house!
All I know is that she's not looking good, she might be nearing her limit
I knew her time was drawing near, her condition was only worsening recently, but I can't let her go without saying…
Time just kept on slipping away and I just wanted it to stop...
My part of the message is 'War.' A conflict between multiple factions
My part of the message is 'Against.' In opposition. To move against, is to resist.
My part of the message is 'Reality.' The truth. The state of which we exist in.

You who deny the truth, do not travel with your eyes shut close, accept the truth and be granted the ability to overcome what may.
Let your rain fall and speak to the children in Sorrow View, combine their message with mine and reveal the truth. You must speak to them in the correct order to finish my message.

You need to learn to grow and absorb what’s happening to you. Speak with my children and make sense of the message that they’re trying to tell and hopefully you’ll grow as they do. Only when you speak to them in the correct order, then my message will become clear.
The message begins as... 
“Denial is…”
Sticking your head in the sand… turning a blind eye… it’s all part of the same black hole… it’ll suck you in if you aren’t careful.
You’ll fall into the black hole if you aren’t careful...
You who opened their eyes and sought the truth through the shadows. You can alleviate the darkness and reveal the path that must be traveled.
Go now, make sure you say what you need to say… and remember, the elder by the markets can help if you need it.
Get ready to face your trials. We all believe in you...
We are here to help you on this journey.
You seem lost young one, do you need some help?
I need to get to Granny’s house but I can’t find the way. The city isn’t normal.

Well Lylah, what you are seeing is The Sorrow, a shadow that distorts reality.
The Sorrow has changed the city into a reflection of itself, a dark and challenging world full of trials that will push you to your limits.

Each of the alleyways around the city centre will push you to confront your own emotions, and once you feel you are ready you may proceed down the alleyway on the opposite end of the market to Granny’s house. To remove the shadow blocking the alley, you will need to face at least one of the challenges before you head over there.

Finally, we who cannot perceive are both pure and corrupted. We can help you, but you need to look beyond the veil. I see you are holding back some tears, let them fall. You'll see a whole new side to this world.

You can see what others can’t. Press the left touch pad to toggle in and out of Sorrow View. While in Sorrow View, speak to other characters in the game to get new info or look around the area to see things differently.

Once youve spoken to them in the correct order my street light will change from red to green.
The message begins as... 
"Denial is..."
To move around the city quickly, pull and hold the left trigger and drag the controller towards yourself.
Press the right touch pad to continue conversation
Remember to check the Sorrow View at each challenge as you may find new information in the different reality.
